= Sidebar Blocks

Sidebar blocks contain aside text displayed outside the normal flow of the document.

== Basic Sidebar Block

****
This is a sidebar block.

It contains aside information that complements the main content.
****

== Sidebar Block with Title

.Sidebar: Additional Information
****
This sidebar has a title.

It can contain multiple paragraphs and other content.
****

== Sidebar Block with Lists

****
Here's a sidebar with a list:

* First point
* Second point
* Third point
****

== Sidebar Block with Formatting

****
This sidebar contains *bold* and _italic_ text.

It can also contain `monospaced` text and links.
****

== Multiple Sidebar Blocks

****
First sidebar block.
****

****
Second sidebar block with different content.
****

== Sidebar Block with ID

[#sidebar-1]
.Sidebar: Reference
****
This sidebar has an ID for cross-referencing.
****

